  "datePublished": "2025-12-26",
  "description": "Necessity is the modality of what must be the case — what holds not just as things happen to be, but in every relevant way things could be. \u0026ldquo;2 + 2 = 4\u0026rdquo; is necessarily true: there is no possible world in which it fails. \u0026ldquo;It is raining in London\u0026rdquo; is contingently true (or false): it depends on circumstances that could have been otherwise. The concept of necessity, and its dual possibility, are the central subjects of modal logic.\n",
  "name": "Necessity",
